The paper discusses the use of Machine Learning techniques to enhance the modeling component of Combinatorial Optimization, which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Optimization (cs.RO). The focus on modeling and the use of ML techniques suggest that the paper could also belong to the subcategories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the mention of uncertainty in the title suggests that the paper could also belong to the subcategory of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
